# Website Customer-Only Import Boundary

`website/` is the Customer + visitor frontend on mount `/website`. It MUST NOT import, reference, or wire any cpanel/supervisor surface. Supervisor is a `cpanel/` concern.

## Forbidden in `website/`

- Importing `src/types/requesters/requesters.cpanel.ts`. The website requester map is `src/types/requesters/requesters.website.ts` only.
- Importing or mirroring `supervisor.graphql` / `gql-types/supervisor.ts`. Website GQL mirror is `base` + `customer` under `src/types/gql/**` only.
- Wiring `FORMS.SUPERVISOR.*` in `src/resources/configs/axios/api.ts`. Customer write path is `FORMS.R` (visitor) + `FORMS.CUSTOMER.R`.
- `AuthedAs = "SUPERVISOR"` or any `supervisor` key in the auth reducer. Website actor is `AuthedAs = "CUSTOMER"` with `auth.customer.permissions`.
- Supervisor socket namespaces or supervisor socket event payloads (`OnWhatsappAccountStatusChanged*`, `OnGroupChatSessionProcess*`, `OnSingleChatSessionMessage*`, `OnNotificationDeleted*`, `OnBulkNotification*`). Website socket namespace is `customer`; events mirror `website/src/types/events.ts` customer payloads only.
- Supervisor/cpanel nav item keys (`customers`, `realEstateCompanies`, `individualSellers`, `projects`, `standaloneUnits`, `orders`, `viewingBookings`, `financialOperations`, `technicalSupport`, `contactMessages`, `supervisors`, `platformSettings`, `accountSettings`) in drawer specs or translations.
- `BASE_URL` pointing at the `/cpanel` mount. Website `BASE_URL` uses `/website` in both test and production (invariant W44).

## Required

- Requesters: `visitor.auth`, `customer.customer`, `customer.notification` from `requesters.website.ts`.
- GQL mirror: `base` + `customer` only.
- Socket: `customer` namespace + customer event payloads.
- `graphql.config.yml` schema lists reference `base.graphql` and (where the subtree hosts customer operations) `customer.graphql` only — never `supervisor.graphql`.

## Why

Cross-platform contamination (cpanel requesters/supervisor mirrors wired into website) silently breaks the actor model, routes, socket, and backend mount. The boundary is enforced at import time; a single guard here prevents a per-caller fix.

